cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.BIO, cs.IT, cs.MM

The paper discusses the design and implementation of synthetic molecular communication systems using biological components as transmitters and receivers. This topic falls under the intersection of several CS sub-disciplines, including neural networks (cs.NE) for modeling biological signaling pathways, systems and control (cs.SY) for designing and optimizing synthetic MCSs, bioinformatics (cs.BIO) for analyzing biological components and their interactions, information theory (cs.IT) for studying the transmission and reception of molecular signals, and multimedia (cs.MM) for exploring the potential applications of synthetic MCSs in areas such as drug delivery and biosensing. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
